text: Nectandra coeloclada is a species of plant in the family Lauraceae. It is endemic to Ecuador. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. ==References== coeloclada Category:Endemic flora of Ecuador Category:Least concern plants Category:Least concern biota of South America Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
